👉 Attacker uploads a file (any extension)
👉 Inside file → JavaScript payload
👉 Server serves it as:

Content-Type: text/plain

👉 Browser guesses (sniffs) and executes it ❌


3️⃣ Browser behavior
❌ Without nosniff

👉 Browser says:

“This looks like HTML/JS”

👉 Executes:

alert(document.cookie)

🔥 XSS happens
